{"type":"message","id":"0005c84f","parentId":"a783b0b9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:14:03.270Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No node processes for the services. The 3103 and 3105 services seem to be running though (they responded to curl earlier). Let me check more carefully.\n\nActually wait - earlier when I curled 3103 and 3105, they responded. But the curl to `/api/score` on 3103 returned \"Cannot GET /api/score\" which is an HTML error page - that means the service IS running but that specific endpoint doesn't exist or requires POST.\n\nLet me check if the services are running with different processes.\n","thinkingSignature":"fe229579a18f5551a8307b55b3b319ca5019bccd9a01ba6e231c89f253d32c72"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3c3xobw2rrhz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"3103|3105|v8|router\" | grep -v grep | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3c3xobw2rrhz_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"lsof -i :3103 -i :3105 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":929,"output":203,"cacheRead":33280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34412,"cost":{"input":0.0002787,"output":0.00024359999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0019968,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0025191}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776179634474,"responseId":"062d8cb233ba786db87e5746c13c4756"}}
