{"type":"message","id":"1bb6cfc2","parentId":"d78f07ac","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:14:44.618Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session transcript contains only tool calls and their results - the human messages themselves aren't stored as `type: \"message\"` in the jsonl. This is because the session was captured with tool results inline. Let me try to find human messages with different approach.\n\nActually - let me check what the most recent summary has vs what the current session actually contains. The issue might be that:\n1. The session-summary hook ran at 23:07 when I started this session, but the hook ran BEFORE the session had meaningful content (at that point the user hadn't said anything yet)\n2. So the summary is just \"(无会话内容)\"\n\nNow at 23:10+, after the user has sent messages in this session, I need to see if the session data was captured correctly.\n\nLet me try a different approach to extract the human messages from the session jsonl.\n","thinkingSignature":"510f3806f3386064065385c91eb9cbcef93c07b606bb70ee5e9933e126bc77bf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oo6b90w1u3q8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/acd88055-6aae-4809-beea-c9239ba74d9e.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nlines = sys.stdin.readlines()\nprint(f'Total lines: {len(lines)}')\n# 检查是否有 human/user 消息\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line: continue\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        msg = d.get('message', {})\n        role = msg.get('role', '')\n        if role in ('human', 'user'):\n            content = msg.get('content', '')\n            if isinstance(content, list):\n                for c in content:\n                    if c.get('type') == 'text':\n                        print(f'[line {i}] HUMAN: {c[\\\"text\\\"][:100]}')\n            elif isinstance(content, str):\n                print(f'[line {i}] HUMAN: {content[:100]}')\n    except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":523,"output":425,"cacheRead":34432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35380,"cost":{"input":0.0001569,"output":0.0005099999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0020659199999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0027328199999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776179668109,"responseId":"062d8cd471b59ebf7ec24a8ab2d0a4ad"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07f74c12","parentId":"1bb6cfc2","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:14:44.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oo6b90w1u3q8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Total lines: 75\n[line 4] HUMAN: A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required \n[line 13] HUMAN: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-u\n[line 16] HUMAN: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-u"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":82,"aggregated":"Total lines: 75\n[line 4] HUMAN: A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required \n[line 13] HUMAN: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-u\n[line 16] HUMAN: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-u","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776179684750}}
{"type":"message","id":"1b4a9572","parentId":"07f74c12","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:15:11.086Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the actual user messages in this session:\n1. \"A new session was started via /new or /reset...\" - this is the system startup prompt\n2. \"Sender (untrusted metadata)...\" - two instances of the openclaw-control-ui sender metadata\n\nSo the session has 3 user messages - the /new trigger, and two control-ui messages. The session-summary hook ran at 23:07 (during the /new) but the session actually has content beyond the /new trigger. However, by the time the hook ran, the session might not have had the additional messages yet.\n\nWait - the session was started at 23:07, and the session-summary was created at 23:07. \n\nLooking at the timeline, the session-summary was written right when the session began, but the actual conversation messages came after - the two control-ui messages at 23:08 and 23:10 are what generated that 23:07 file with \"(无会话内容)\" since the hook only captured the initial state.\n\nThe real issue is that the hook triggers on the /new command itself, not after the session ends, so it's capturing the empty session state before any对话 actually happens. Looking at the hook's `run()` function, it checks for command types like \"new\" or \"reset\" to trigger the summary generation.\n\nThe reason we got \"(无会话内容)\" is likely because the session file resolution failed - the `resolveSessionFile` function may have returned a path with no actual content, causing the hook to default to the fallback message instead of extracting real session data.\n\nThe core issue is that this was a fresh /new with no previous session to reference, so `previousSessionEntry` is empty. The hook tried to fall back to `sessionEntry` but webchat sessions don't store conversation history in .jsonl files - they're stored in the gateway database instead. So the hook couldn't find any accumulated conversation to summarize, which is why it returned \"(无会话内容)\" rather than actual dialogue content.\n\nThe ephemeral directory is also empty because the v8 classifier wasn't capturing events for this session. However, the bootstrap mechanism did successfully locate and inject the session-summary file into context, which means that part of the pipeline is functioning correctly. The full session-summary → bootstrap → LLM chain only works when there's an actual previous session to pull from; on a fresh /new, there's nothing to inject yet.\n\nThis is the expected behavior for a brand-new session, and the system performed correctly by generating an empty summary rather than failing. The real test would come from running /new after having a conversation, then executing /new again to see if the previous session's content gets properly injected.\n\nNow I should report these findings to the user.\n","thinkingSignature":"d8e17c0bb78b2a5ee15088e808cee1c42ecf9cd37f43ac6b0e133e95ac59e55d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ecdfcggl39qx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/acd88055-6aae-4809-beea-c9239ba74d9e.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nlines = sys.stdin.readlines()\n# 看最后几行的时间戳\nfor line in lines[-5:]:\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line: continue\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        ts = d.get('timestamp', d.get('time', ''))\n        t = d.get('type', '')\n        print(f'{ts} [{t}]')\n    except: pass\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":382,"output":719,"cacheRead":34944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36045,"cost":{"input":0.0001146,"output":0.0008627999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00209664,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00307404}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776179684764,"responseId":"062d8ce40e632b30a8e29c821bf3ecd7"}}
